This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with generating natural language text from Abstract Meaning Representation (AMR). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also involves the evaluation of the generated text, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of sound and music computing (cs.SD).
